    "notes": "K2 V active young dwarf, second-nearest planet host after Proxima (d = 3.220 +/- 0.001 pc). Has direct interferometric angular diameter -- both Di Folco 2007 (VLTI/VINCI) and Baines & Armstrong 2012 (PAVO@CHARA) resolved theta_LD ~ 2.12-2.15 mas. Phase 2 recommends Baines 2012 (R = 0.735 +/- 0.005 Rsun from PAVO@CHARA theta_LD = 2.126 +/- 0.014 mas + Hipparcos parallax 310.94 +/- 0.16 mas; Teff = 5039 +/- 126 K from L_bol + theta_LD Stefan-Boltzmann inversion; L = 0.320 +/- 0.011 Lsun bolometric) for the radius/Teff/L trio because the same paper derives all three self-consistently from theta_LD + bolometric flux + parallax (most-direct method). Earlier Phase 3 cited Rosenthal 2021 SED-fit R = 0.759 +/- 0.012 Rsun as primary; the ~3% offset traces to direct-angular-diameter vs SED-fit method choice. The DB raw teff_k = 5180 K (Gaia-DR3-derived photometric proxy) is also higher than the interferometric value by ~140 K. Mass = 0.82 +/- 0.02 Msun (Llop-Sayson 2021 joint RV + Hipparcos IAD + Gaia DR2 + multi-epoch vortex coronagraphy fit; schema method 'evolutionary_model' is the closest tier-allowed match for this joint dynamical-fit-with-stellar-evolution-prior procedure) is the modern canonical pick. Age 0.44 +/- 0.10 Gyr (Mamajek & Hillenbrand 2008 activity-rotation joint isochrone+CaIIHK+Xray+rotation fit) is the published symmetric formal uncertainty -- but gyrochrone systematics at this age are factor-of-2 and the literature spread runs 0.2-0.9 Gyr; Llop-Sayson 2021 adopts 400-800 Myr as the host-star prior. Donahue 1996 P_rot = 11.20 +/- 0.05 d from 14-yr Mt Wilson Ca II HK Project is the canonical eps Eri rotation period; schema method 'photometric_variability' is the closest tier-allowed match for periodic-flux-timeseries rotation extraction (Ca II HK index is the flux). Croll 2006 MOST broadband photometry 11.45 d independent confirmation. Activity log R'HK = -4.39 (Zechmeister 2013 modern HARPS epoch) places eps Eri in the active K dwarf locus; Metcalfe 2013 resolved dual chromospheric cycles 2.95 +/- 0.03 yr (short) + 12.7 +/- 0.3 yr (long), and Coffaro 2020 confirms the 2.95-yr cycle in 17 years of XMM monitoring with log L_X cycle 28.3-28.9 cgs. No asteroseismology: Bonanno 2008 attempted RV-based mode detection but the activity floor swamps p-mode amplitudes."
